
.TH NEONSEC-RULES 5 "2025-09-05" "neonsec" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
neonsec-rules \- JSON rule specification for neonsec
.SH DESCRIPTION
Rules are provided as a JSON document with a top-level array key `rules`. Each rule contains:
`name`, `when` (array of predicates with `field`, `op`, `value`), `group_by`, `within_sec`,
a count or sum condition, and an `emit` object (`type`, `details`). See `schemas/rules.schema.json`.
